english:
  title: Night Musings
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Fevered, I sit sleepless through the night—
    White streaks silver my temples, desolate and thin.
    Tea murmurs in the small kettle's complaint,
    Lamplight traces the curves of an old, worn vessel.
    Moonlight pierces the curtain, entering my chamber,
    Wind shakes the paper window, making it cry.
    Having witnessed all the affairs of humankind,
    My idle sorrow fills my breast to bursting.
  footnotes:
    - The poem uses the sounds of daily life—boiling tea, flickering lamplight, wind and paper—as anchors for contemplation, a technique common in Korean literati poetry.
    - The speaker's sickness and sleeplessness are not merely physical states but gateways to philosophical reflection on the human condition.
